						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="article" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Dryland-agriculture/Related-developments/Making-dryland-research-matter-Addressing-need-for-European-African-partnership-for-Ethiopia-and-Niger" title="Making dryland research matter : Addressing need for European-African partnership for Ethiopia and Niger" alt="article">Making dryland research matter : Addressing need for European-African partnership for Ethiopia and Niger</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/dryland-agriculture/301196-1-eng-GB/Dryland-agriculture.jpg" rel="lightbox[]">	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	Dryland Africa is faced with many challenges, like water shortage, food crisis, erosion, land degradation and desertification. Concerns exist on the contribution of research to the solution to these challenges: farmer knowledge might be underappreciated and duplication and contradiction might be present in the policies and interventions. CTA has commissioned a group of students from Wageningen University to reflect on these issues. </p>
							<p><span class="date">21/05/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="article" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Dryland-agriculture/Related-developments/Making-dryland-research-matter-Addressing-need-for-European-African-partnership-for-Ethiopia-and-Niger">Read more...</a>
